A '''tranny chaser''' is a term used by some to denote a person who loves or is attracted to [[transsexual]] or [[transgendered]] people.  It is usually applied to non-transgendered men who are attracted to pre- or non-operative [[transwomen]].  In common usage, it is seen by many in the applicable group as offensive, with terms such as "admirer" being preferred instead.

Some have suggested that the root of men's attraction to transwomen lies in [[Psychological_repression|repressed]] [[homosexuality]] or [[bisexuality]].  However, there are no known studies on this phenomenon. Many transgendered people and their admirers object to this idea, as it assumes that transwomen are actually just [[crossdressing]] men.  See also [[Homosexuality and transgender]] for more information on the difficulty in defining relationships involving transgendered people as [[homosexuality|homosexual]] or [[heterosexuality|heterosexual]].

